  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Something I noticed while debugging #570 and writing #676 is that Docker has a native `HEALTHCHECK` command and `docker-compose` has a native `healthcheck` configuration option. There is a nice sample repo [here](https://github.com/peter-evans/docker-compose-healthcheck) that demonstrates how we might be able to use it. [Here](https://blog.sixeyed.com/docker-healthchecks-why-not-to-use-curl-or-iwr/) is an opinionated article about how health checks should work too. We might benefit from this.",
