    "body": "Came across this issue and dove into it a bit because I'm trying to get familiar with the repo ðŸ˜„ . After diving in a bit, I suspect that following a [wait-for-it.sh](https://docs.docker.com/compose/startup-order/) type strategy might work better than using `healthcheck` for the startup race conditions referenced in the issue. `Healthcheck` I believe is primarily designed to tell when a service is healthy/ unhealthy and doesn't do any blocking like `wait-for-it.sh` does. I'm a noob to the repo so very well might be off base here.",
